public class Wavelength
extends Quantity

Wavelength, an object to minimize problems with wavelength units

This code was developed by NASA, Goddard Space Flight Center, Code 587 for the Scientist's Expert Assistant (SEA) project for Next Generation Space Telescope (NGST). This class manages wavelengths and provides a means to easily track different units Users can set a static default units and then retrieve a wavelength value (as double) by calling getLength().. or user can requests wavelengths in one of the following specific wavelengths: getLengthMicrons(), getLength( Wavelength.METER), getLengthAngstroms(), or getLengthNanometers() On construction, the normal constructor is Wavelength( value, units).
